### Failure Pattern Recording

When a CI test fails, lint check fails, or any reproducible error is encountered during this phase, record it **before** moving on:

```bash
harness save-failure --json \
  --task task-NNN \
  --phase <current-phase> \
  --category <ci-failure|test-failure|lint-error|type-error|build-error|runtime-error|other> \
  --summary "Short description of the failure" \
  --error-output "Relevant error output (first 500 chars, no secrets)" \
  --root-cause "Root cause if known" \
  --fix "Fix applied if any"
```

Replace `task-NNN`, `<current-phase>`, and field values with actuals.  The `--json` flag returns a machine-readable JSON object for downstream consumption.

